Ecco le mie impressioni dopo diverse settimane di utilizzo.Design e CostruzioneIl POCO X6 Pro presenta un design elegante e moderno, con una costruzione solida che conferisce una sensazione di robustezza. La parte posteriore in vetro e il telaio in metallo offrono un aspetto premium che è difficile da trovare in questa fascia di prezzo. Il dispositivo è disponibile in diverse colorazioni vivaci che lo rendono attraente a prima vista.#### DisplayIl display del POCO X6 Pro è uno dei suoi punti di forza. Con un pannello AMOLED da 6,67 pollici e una risoluzione Full HD+, le immagini sono nitide e i colori vivaci. La frequenza di aggiornamento di 120 Hz garantisce una fluidità eccezionale nelle animazioni e nello scrolling, migliorando l'esperienza utente sia nei giochi che nella navigazione quotidiana.#### PrestazioniEquipaggiato con un processore Snapdragon 870 e 8 GB di RAM, il POCO X6 Pro offre prestazioni eccellenti. Le applicazioni si aprono rapidamente e il multitasking è fluido. Ho testato diversi giochi ad alte prestazioni e il telefono ha gestito tutto senza problemi, senza rallentamenti o surriscaldamenti eccessivi. Anche le applicazioni più impegnative funzionano senza intoppi, rendendo questo dispositivo ideale per gli utenti più esigenti.#### FotocameraIl comparto fotografico del POCO X6 Pro è sorprendentemente buono per la sua fascia di prezzo. La fotocamera principale da 64 MP cattura immagini dettagliate e vivide in condizioni di buona illuminazione. La modalità notturna migliora significativamente le foto scattate in ambienti poco illuminati, riducendo il rumore e migliorando la nitidezza. La fotocamera grandangolare e il sensore macro aggiungono versatilità al sistema fotografico, permettendo di catturare una varietà di scatti diversi.#### BatteriaLa batteria da 5000 mAh del POCO X6 Pro offre un'autonomia eccellente. Con un uso moderato, il telefono dura facilmente due giorni con una sola carica. Anche con un uso intensivo, tra cui sessioni di gaming e streaming video, il dispositivo riesce a coprire un'intera giornata senza problemi. La ricarica rapida da 33W è un ulteriore vantaggio, permettendo di ricaricare completamente la batteria in circa un'ora.#### SoftwareIl POCO X6 Pro utilizza MIUI, la skin personalizzata di Xiaomi basata su Android. L'interfaccia è ricca di funzionalità e personalizzazioni, anche se potrebbe risultare un po' pesante per chi preferisce un'esperienza Android più stock. Tuttavia, MIUI è fluida e offre molte opzioni per adattare il telefono alle proprie esigenze.#### PrezzoIl POCO X6 Pro offre un rapporto qualità-prezzo eccezionale. Con specifiche e prestazioni paragonabili a dispositivi di fascia più alta, il prezzo competitivo lo rende una scelta eccellente per chi cerca un telefono potente senza spendere una fortuna.#### ConclusioniIn conclusione, il POCO X6 Pro è uno smartphone che offre prestazioni elevate, un display eccellente e una buona qualità costruttiva a un prezzo molto competitivo. È ideale per chi cerca un dispositivo versatile, capace di gestire sia le attività quotidiane che i giochi più impegnativi. Consiglio vivamente il POCO X6 Pro a chiunque cerchi un telefono di alta qualità senza spendere troppo.

I am coming from an S10 which has served me incredibly well for the past 5 years but I wanted a bigger screen because my sight isn't what it used to be. I was between the Ultra and the plus and decided to go with the ultra for the snapdragon and the anti glare display, but now I regret not going with the regular 24 and saving 20K in the process. The gain in screen size, even compared to the standard S10, isn't that big of a deal and cannot justify the overall size and bulk.  I also hate the fact that they changed the UI navigation gestures, the new gestures are hit and miss but that applies to all S24 models.It was a good bundle deal from amazon though who generously threw in the original silicone case besides the galaxy buds fe and the free 2 year screen insurance samsung egypt offers early buyers. The free screen insurance is a little tricky to activate though. You need to log into your samsung members app, discover, tap the benefits tab and select the screen insurance, then manually register for it. The item listed here is the phone ONLY, if you are trying to buy the BUNDLE like I did, it's a different listing and will be clearly titled bundle. Phone and accessories were delivered together the same day. Delivery required a PIN as with all high value items. All items were sealed as expected from amazon, and the phone's warranty card was wedged in the box as usual. This is only for your own assurance, since from experience, you don't need the card for warranty claims as Samsung Egypt can look up the local warranty information if any with the phone's serial number.If you know exactly what you are getting and have used a recent ultra or note phone, go right ahead, you will not be disappointed aside from the new navigation gestures if you use them instead of the buttons like me; but if you are on the fence and trying to decide which S24 model to buy, I suggest you see them in person first. I know I would choose differently if I did. The anti reflective screen glass on the ultra really works but it also diffuses the pixel light and makes the display look a little bit like an LCD backlit display not an OLED. I really recommend you check out the phone in person first before dropping 66K on it. I am not happy with my purchase.

I was between the Ultra and the plus and decided to go with the ultra for the snapdragon and the anti glare display, but now I regret not going with the regular 24 and saving 20K in the process. I also hate the fact that they changed the UI navigation gestures, the new gestures are hit and miss but that applies to all S24 models.It was a good bundle deal from amazon though who generously threw in the original silicone case besides the galaxy buds fe and the free 2 year screen insurance samsung egypt offers early buyers. The free screen insurance is a little tricky to activate though. You need to log into your samsung members app, discover, tap the benefits tab and select the screen insurance, then manually register for it. The item listed here is the phone ONLY, if you are trying to buy the BUNDLE like I did, it's a different listing and will be clearly titled bundle. Phone and accessories were delivered together the same day. Delivery required a PIN as with all high value items. All items were sealed as expected from amazon, and the phone's warranty card was wedged in the box as usual. This is only for your own assurance, since from experience, you don't need the card for warranty claims as Samsung Egypt can look up the local warranty information if any with the phone's serial number.If you know exactly what you are getting and have used a recent ultra or note phone, go right ahead, you will not be disappointed aside from the new navigation gestures if you use them instead of the buttons like me; but if you are on the fence and trying to decide which S24 model to buy, I suggest you see them in person first. I know I would choose differently if I did. The anti reflective screen glass on the ultra really works but it also diffuses the pixel light and makes the display look a little bit like an LCD backlit display not an OLED. I really recommend you check out the phone in person first before dropping 66K on it. I am not happy with my purchase.

I also hate the fact that they changed the UI navigation gestures, the new gestures are hit and miss but that applies to all S24 models.It was a good bundle deal from amazon though who generously threw in the original silicone case besides the galaxy buds fe and the free 2 year screen insurance samsung egypt offers early buyers. The free screen insurance is a little tricky to activate though. You need to log into your samsung members app, discover, tap the benefits tab and select the screen insurance, then manually register for it. The item listed here is the phone ONLY, if you are trying to buy the BUNDLE like I did, it's a different listing and will be clearly titled bundle. Phone and accessories were delivered together the same day. Delivery required a PIN as with all high value items. All items were sealed as expected from amazon, and the phone's warranty card was wedged in the box as usual. This is only for your own assurance, since from experience, you don't need the card for warranty claims as Samsung Egypt can look up the local warranty information if any with the phone's serial number.If you know exactly what you are getting and have used a recent ultra or note phone, go right ahead, you will not be disappointed aside from the new navigation gestures if you use them instead of the buttons like me; but if you are on the fence and trying to decide which S24 model to buy, I suggest you see them in person first. I know I would choose differently if I did. The anti reflective screen glass on the ultra really works but it also diffuses the pixel light and makes the display look a little bit like an LCD backlit display not an OLED. I really recommend you check out the phone in person first before dropping 66K on it. I am not happy with my purchase.

I was between the Ultra and the plus and decided to go with the ultra for the snapdragon and the anti glare display, but now I regret not going with the regular 24 and saving 20K in the process. I also hate the fact that they changed the UI navigation gestures, the new gestures are hit and miss but that applies to all S24 models.It was a good bundle deal from amazon though who generously threw in the original silicone case besides the galaxy buds fe and the free 2 year screen insurance samsung egypt offers early buyers. The free screen insurance is a little tricky to activate though. You need to log into your samsung members app, discover, tap the benefits tab and select the screen insurance, then manually register for it. The item listed here is the phone ONLY, if you are trying to buy the BUNDLE like I did, it's a different listing and will be clearly titled bundle. Phone and accessories were delivered together the same day. Delivery required a PIN as with all high value items. All items were sealed as expected from amazon, and the phone's warranty card was wedged in the box as usual. This is only for your own assurance, since from experience, you don't need the card for warranty claims as Samsung Egypt can look up the local warranty information if any with the phone's serial number.If you know exactly what you are getting and have used a recent ultra or note phone, go right ahead, you will not be disappointed aside from the new navigation gestures if you use them instead of the buttons like me; but if you are on the fence and trying to decide which S24 model to buy, I suggest you see them in person first. I know I would choose differently if I did. The anti reflective screen glass on the ultra really works but it also diffuses the pixel light and makes the display look a little bit like an LCD backlit display not an OLED. I really recommend you check out the phone in person first before dropping 66K on it. I am not happy with my purchase.

Read more"}, {'Reviewer Name': 'T M', 'Rating': '4.0 out of 5 stars', 'Title': 'HUGE', 'Date': 'Reviewed in Egypt on 28 February 2024', 'Review Body': "It's a great phone but absolutely humongous and a pain to carry or use with one hand, and I have big hands. I am coming from an S10 which has served me incredibly well for the past 5 years but I wanted a bigger screen because my sight isn't what it used to be. I was between the Ultra and the plus and decided to go with the ultra for the snapdragon and the anti glare display, but now I regret not going with the regular 24 and saving 20K in the process. The gain in screen size, even compared to the standard S10, isn't that big of a deal and cannot justify the overall size and bulk.  I also hate the fact that they changed the UI navigation gestures, the new gestures are hit and miss but that applies to all S24 models.It was a good bundle deal from amazon though who generously threw in the original silicone case besides the galaxy buds fe and the free 2 year screen insurance samsung egypt offers early buyers. The free screen insurance is a little tricky to activate though. You need to log into your samsung members app, discover, tap the benefits tab and select the screen insurance, then manually register for it. The item listed here is the phone ONLY, if you are trying to buy the BUNDLE like I did, it's a different listing and will be clearly titled bundle. Phone and accessories were delivered together the same day. Delivery required a PIN as with all high value items. All items were sealed as expected from amazon, and the phone's warranty card was wedged in the box as usual. This is only for your own assurance, since from experience, you don't need the card for warranty claims as Samsung Egypt can look up the local warranty information if any with the phone's serial number.If you know exactly what you are getting and have used a recent ultra or note phone, go right ahead, you will not be disappointed aside from the new navigation gestures if you use them instead of the buttons like me; but if you are on the fence and trying to decide which S24 model to buy, I suggest you see them in person first. I know I would choose differently if I did. The anti reflective screen glass on the ultra really works but it also diffuses the pixel light and makes the display look a little bit like an LCD backlit display not an OLED. I really recommend you check out the phone in person first before dropping 66K on it. I am not happy with my purchase.

The performance is indistinguishable in day to day usage when compared to SD 8 Gen 3 on a OnePlus 12 with UFS 4.0. Even though the 12R has a UFS 3.1 storage, you are unlikely to notice any difference whatsoever without running benchmarks or checking the specifications. In real life day to day usage, I have not found any difference and I am a power user who uses a lot of applications and use the phone over 8 Hours a day.- The vapour chamber handles the cooling very well which keeps the device at excellent temperature even when playing games for an extended duration. It almost never goes over 38c.- The display has the same features as the OnePlus 12 (the resolution is relatively lower but it's not noticeable to the naked eye without magnification) and this is one of the best displays that you will come across. The HDR performance is also some of the best I have seen and it is a completely different experience. This can also be seen in the HDR shots taken with cameras. I'd suggest going to a OnePlus experience center and searching for 12K HDR videos on YouTube to get a better idea. Note that the 4,500 nits mentioned is only the HDR brightness at a small white portion of the display under sunlight. This is NOT the max brightness of the full display. But it is bright enough to use under direct sunlight.- Battery life is very impressive with over 8 hours of SOT and the 100W included charger fully charges it in about 35 mins.- Also love that the display can be used even when your hands are wet unlike most other smartphones- The bezels are extremely slim and the chin is smaller than the one on the OnePlus 12. I do wish it was equal all around though.Rather than cons, I'll just mention what it lacks.- Wireless charging- Telephoto cameraThat's pretty much it. If you are looking for a smooth and reliable device with solid performance, battery life, fast charging, decent cameras and display experience, I would easily recommend this. Read more'}, {'Reviewer Name': '75in4u', 'Rating': 'N/A', 'Title': 'N/A', 'Date': 'Reviewed in Italy on 19 August 2017', 'Review Body': "Ho acquistato questo prodotto dopo aver avuto un Sony ed un Bose della stessa fascia di prezzo (rispettivamente rubato e perduto) e già appena disinballato è risultato molto bello (sopratutto perchè a dirlo è stata mia moglie senza sapere ancora cosa fosse), il caricabatterie ha lo spinotto, meno pratico ed universale dell' usb ma molto più veloce nel ricaricarlo. Ha l' NFC quindi basta appoggiare il telefono (se avete l' NFC) sopra alla cassa per 3 secondi e si accoppia tramite bluetooth (molto scenico oltre che comodo), si ricarica in circa 3 ore e ne dura quasi 8 con volume quasi al massimo. Parliamo ora della qualità audio, viste le dimensioni fa il suo dovere egregiamente ha un suono molto pieno e spaziale rispetto soprattutto al bose, ha dei bassi abbastanza frenati e presenti come il sony ma lo trovo molto più dettagliato di entrambi, la massima pressione sonoro con il volume al massimo non eguaglia quella del bose (di pochissimo) ma in compenso non presenta quell' effetto di musica in scatola. Dei 3 che ho avuto è sicuramente quello che suona meglio e poi non dimenticate che è anche molto bello, brava Edifier.
